 on spec.  As the wx increased the Master was forced to heave anchor and run wx patterns while still awaiting orders.  After 1.7 days, the ok to sail was given and she proceeded without issue to Las Minas for discharge.  As it turned out, tank space was the issue for the jet.  Chevron then asked if we could sail back to Pascagoula after discharge 2/3rd of the jet parcel.  We agreed due to our solid relationship, but have requested a laytime credit of 20hrs for lost time given that would be approx. time spent if we had in fact discharged, and also loaded the same qty on her next voyage.  Surprisingly Chevron agreed provided we supply support\u2026which of course we did.  All in all voyage is spot on with the generation with main increase being demurrage and claiming deviation time/bunkers for wx pattern due to chrts request to remain at an unsafe port.\nImprovements:  None to note\n\n\nFIXTURE NOTE\n\n2nd voyage of the extended CVC to Chevron with 2\u002B2\u002B2 voyages option at $735 k L/S and 21,500 usd Dem. No bunker hedge. \n\nVessel\tStena Performance\nVoy#\t2217\nFix#\tCVX CVC #8 USG/CBS\nC/P Date\tMay 19, 2022\nCharterer\tCHEVRON\nBroker\tAFFINITY\nStart\tBahia Las Minas\nLoad\tPascagoula\nDischarge\tBahia Las Minas\nCargo\t45,000 mt CPP\nLay/Can\tSep 21-23, 2022 (00:00-16:00)\nRate\t$735,000\nComm\tCharterer: 2.5%, Broker: 1.25%, Agent: 1%\nTCE\nPnL\nSB PnL\t$21,547.04 for 13.5 days\n$81k usd Bss 15,5 pd \n$40.5k usd \nDemurrage\t$21,500.00"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-09-20T18:09:17.397","modifiedByFull":"Webb, Alex","remark":""}],"offhireList":[{"id":192604,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":104303,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}